# Linked to .cursor/rules/git-commits.mdc and commitlint.config.mjs
# If those files are updated, update this file to match.

When generating a git commit message, always follow this exact format:

  type(scope): short description

Types: feat, fix, chore, docs, refactor, style, test, perf, ci, build, hotfix, revert
Scopes: web, cms, crawler, deps, ci, docs

Rules:
- Scope is REQUIRED — never omit it
- Description must be lowercase
- No period at the end
- Under 100 characters total

Examples:
  feat(web): add hero section
  fix(cms): resolve slug query
  chore(deps): upgrade astro
